2. The word signifies sometimes an Inquisition into the state of Affairs by a judicial Process, as Exod. 3.16. I have surely visited you, and seen that which is done unto you; that is, I have enquired into, examined, and consider'd your case: Job 31.14. When God visiteth, what shall I answer him? Not that God needs any such thing to inform him, for he knows all the wickedness in the World as soon as it is acted; but he speaks after the manner of Men, for the clearer manifestation of his own Justice, and the greater terror to them: as it was in the case of Sodom,

whose sins cried to Heaven;
Gen. 18.21. yet says God, I will go down and see whether they have done altogether according to the cry which is come unto me: an expression rather of Justice than want of Intelligence.

